2026-05-10 01:45:51 GMT | claude:claude-opus-4-7 | EDIT | scripts/capture.py | Add --original-year override flag for misreporting Discogs masters
    User authorized: "2. Yes" (in response to my surfacing that Discogs's Ummagumma master returned year=1974 and title='Ummagumma Vol. 2', which is wrong).
    New flag: --original-year INT. When provided, overrides the captured record's `original_release_year` field after build_album_record() returns. Print confirms when override fires. Compile-checked.
    Use case: Discogs master records sometimes carry stale or incorrect data (wrong title, wrong year) for older albums where the editor used a reissue series as the canonical master. Without the override, the JSON would carry Discogs's wrong year and the library sort would place the album in the wrong era.

